7.2     [High] Vesu Gateway uses the same default pool ID for every withdrawal
     File(s): vesu_gateway.cairo
     Description: During withdrawals from Vesu, users specify from which pool they want to withdraw using the context field in the Withdraw
     struct:

1    fn withdraw(ref self: ContractState, instruction: @Withdraw) {
 2       // ...
 3       if instruction.context.is_some() {
 4           let mut context_bytes: Span<felt252> = (*instruction.context).unwrap();
 5           let vesu_context: VesuContext = Serde::deserialize(ref context_bytes).unwrap();
 6           if vesu_context.pool_id != Zero::zero() {
 7               pool_id = vesu_context.pool_id;
 8           }
 9           if vesu_context.position_counterpart_token != Zero::zero() {
10               debt_asset = vesu_context.position_counterpart_token;
11           }
12       }
13       // ...

     Later, contract needs to call the correct vToken address to convert user’s shares to assets. However, the vToken retrieved is not from the
     user’s specified pool_id:

1    fn modify_collateral_for(
 2       ref self: ContractState,
 3       pool_id: felt252,
 4       collateral_asset: ContractAddress,
 5       debt_asset: ContractAddress,
 6       user: ContractAddress,
 7       collateral_amount: i257,
 8   ) -> UpdatePositionResponse {
 9       // ...
10       // If this is negative, it means withdraw
11       if collateral_amount.is_negative() {
12           // @audit doesn't pass user's pool id
13           let vtoken = self.get_vtoken_for_collateral(collateral_asset);
14
15            let erc4626 = IERC4626Dispatcher { contract_address: vtoken };
16            let requested_shares = erc4626.convert_to_shares(collateral_amount.abs());
17            let available_shares = vesu_context.position.collateral_shares;
18            assert(available_shares > 0, 'No-collateral');
19            // ...
20   }

1    fn get_vtoken_for_collateral(
 2       self: @ContractState, collateral: ContractAddress,
 3   ) -> ContractAddress {
 4       let vesu_singleton_dispatcher = ISingletonDispatcher {
 5           contract_address: self.vesu_singleton.read(),
 6       };
 7       // @audit uses contract's default pool id
 8       let poolId = self.pool_id.read();
 9       let extensionForPool = vesu_singleton_dispatcher.extension(poolId);
10       let extension = IDefaultExtensionCLDispatcher { contract_address: extensionForPool };
11       extension.v_token_for_collateral_asset(poolId, collateral)
12   }

     As a result, the wrong vToken address is used to retrieve information about the user’s available shares and final withdraw amount.
     Impact: Users are unable to withdraw from their required pools as the transaction will revert if they don’t have any shares in the default
     pool_id. Also, users who have shares in that pool will withdraw assets from that pool even if they specified another pool.
     Recommendation(s): Pass users’ pool_id to the get_vtoken_for_collateral(...) function and use that to retrieve the extension
     contract address.

                                                                                                                                             8
     CODESPECT

     Status: Fixed
